      "writtenOn": "2021-05-10T19:32:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are there clients with their own subclasses? I wonder if we\u0027d be better off forcing the implementor of each SkPathEffect to have to think about this by making it pure virtual. Might work better if the query and computation were one function, maybe like:\n\n virtual bool computeFastBounds(SkRect* inOutBounds) const \u003d 0;",
