      "writtenOn": "2021-05-10T20:29:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I could not find any clients that subclassed SkPathEffect. I do like your function signature better, but SkPaint\u0027s computeFastBounds API is split into two functions as well. To remain compatible with that, I\u0027ll have SkPathEffect::computeFastBounds() specified so that \u0027inOutBounds\u0027 can be null, in which case it just reports the bool w/o computing the bounds.  If SkPaint\u0027s API can be cleaned up similarly, then we can remove the null support.  \n\nDoes that sound reasonable?",
      "parentUuid": "703cebd0_0f82d19e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 186,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 186,
        "endChar": 88
      },
